items.abstract: <jats:p><jats:italic>Background</jats:italic>. Metalloproteinases (MMPs) play a pivotal role during the process of trophoblast invasion and placentation. The appearance of five functional single-nucleotide polymorphisms (SNP) in the genes of the metalloproteinases most commonly implicated in the implantation process may influence the development of preeclampsia. <jats:italic>Methods</jats:italic>. Blood samples were collected from 86 mothers and 86 children after preeclampsia and 85 mothers and 85 children with uncomplicated pregnancies. The distribution of genotypes for −1607 1G/2G <jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic>, −735 C/T <jats:italic>MMP2</jats:italic>, −1306 C/T <jats:italic>MMP2</jats:italic>, −1171 5A/6A <jats:italic>MMP3</jats:italic>, and −1562C/T <jats:italic>MMP9</jats:italic> polymorphisms was determined by RFLP-PCR. <jats:italic>Results</jats:italic>. The occurrence of 1G/1G <jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic> or 5A/5A <jats:italic>MMP3</jats:italic> genotype in the mother or 1G/1G <jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic> or 5A/6A <jats:italic>MMP3</jats:italic> genotype in the child is associated with preeclampsia development. Moreover, simultaneous maternal and fetal 1G/1G homozygosity increases the risk of preeclampsia development 2.39-fold and the set of maternal 5A/5A and fetal 5A/6A <jats:italic>MMP3</jats:italic> genotypes by over 4.5 times. No association between the carriage of studied <jats:italic>MMP2</jats:italic> or <jats:italic>MMP9</jats:italic> polymorphisms and the predisposition to preeclampsia was found. <jats:italic>Conclusion</jats:italic>. The maternal 1G/1G <jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic> and 5A/5A <jats:italic>MMP3</jats:italic> and fetal 1G/1G <jats:italic>MMP1</jats:italic> and 5A/6A <jats:italic>MMP3</jats:italic> gene polymorphisms may be strong genetic markers of preeclampsia, occurring either individually or together.</jats:p>
title: Association of Maternal and Fetal Single-Nucleotide Polymorphisms in Metalloproteinase (MMP1, MMP2, MMP3, and MMP9) Genes with Preeclampsia
